. Sharing personal stories from her own experience as a young activist, as a mother, and as a teacher, Seely offers a practical guide to getting involved, taking action, and waging successful events and campaigns. The second edition addresses more themes and topics than before, including gender and sexuality, self-esteem, reproductive health, sexual violence, body image and acceptance, motherhood and family, and intersections of identities, such as race, gender, class, and sexualities. Fight Like a Girl is an invaluable introduction to both feminism and activism, defining the core tenets of feminism, the key challenges both within and outside the feminist movement, and the steps we can take to create a more socially just world.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Jul 2021) 0aFeminism. 0aWomen's rights. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Women's Studies.2bisacsh  aEqual Rights Amendment.  aLGBTQ.  aReproductive Justice.  aSupreme Court.  aTitle IX.  aabortion.  aabuse.  aactivism.  aally.  abirth control.  abody image.  abody politic.  achange.  adisability.  adiscrimination.  aeating disorders.  afat activism.  afeminism.  afeminist movement.  agender identity.  aglobal violence.  aglobalization.  agrape boycott.  agrassroots.  aharassment.  ahomophobia.  ainclusive.  aintersectionality.  aleadership.  aliveable wage.  amasculinity.  amedia.  amenstruation.  apatriarchy.  apersonal politics.  apolitics.  aprivilege.  arace.  aracism.  arape.  aself-care.  aself-exam.  asexual assault.  asexuality.  asocial justice.  asuffrage.  asweatshop.  atimeline.  atrafficking.  atrans.  aviolence.  awaves.  aweight.  awomen.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertNew York University Press Complete eBook-Package 2019z978311072272740uhttps: